rd.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how soon can you begin to communicate?</span><hr size=1> It depends on how new you are and your groupmates are to EQ.  I was in several groups where no one had a common tongue (before 19 for me).  Some of them worked great -- everyone knew what to do, no talking really required.  One was pretty bad; new war and new cleric.  War would attack anything he saw and wouldn't move to avoid BS'ing from adds.  Cleric tanked and nuked instead of med'ing and healing.  Lotta zoning for that group.<br>
<br>
For communication purposes, it depends on luck.  Even 1 skill in a language is enough to sometimes get a nearly clear sentence out -- maybe 1 in 50 tries for that, though.  It's generaly pretty bad until you get to at least &quot;very good&quot; at 80 or &quot;excellent&quot; at 90.  Expect at least one word to be garbled on up through 99; 100 is the only sure thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=enheduanna>Enheduanna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 7:15:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how soon can you begin to communicate?</span><hr size=1> I found that repeating the exact same sentance (via Shift-UpArrow) helps comprehension a lot, even when the language is unknown. You can often get the idea across by saying<br>
<br>
repeat<br>
repeat<br>
repeat<br>
<br>
Most people get the idea, and start repeating. Then you have a better chance of puzzling out the words by looking at the differeneces in mangling. Also, the language mangler doesn't appear to insert uppercase letters, so if you both use all-caps then you can tell which letters were changed.<br>
<br>
And yes, I found that a rating of average was enough to convey essential communication. It didn't work too well for banter and the like, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upriestessnaeneori.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Priestess Naeneori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 7:37:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how soon can you begin to communicate?</span><hr size=1> if you have a point in the other persons language...you can switch to that language &amp; do an emote that they can understand as well.....that might help in groups...<br>
<br>
/em wishes the tank would call for INC...<br>
<br>
you get the idea.... <p><img src="http://noirdaila.homestead.com/files/NaenSign.JPG"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 5:20:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: how soon can you begin to communicate?</span><hr size=1> There's a real-life skill involved.  It's the same skill that lets you communicate in English* with someone who does not speak English* very well, or has a strong accent (*or any language, really).<br>
<br>
Having travelled a bit in Asia and Eastern Europe, I can attest that some people have an ability to clearly understand what would sound like utter gibberish to most English-speakers. The converse is also true.  I've met many Americans who were baffled by a London accent, hard as that may be to believe.  It's like they're hearing Greek spoken.<br>
<br>
But back to Everquest. Let me give you to examples.  Myself, I can understand someone perfectly when my language skill is only Good.  For my own sake, it's hardly even worth improving my language skills past Good.  On the other hand, there are people on this board who swear they have trouble understanding someone whose language skill is anything less than Master.  Go figure.<br>
<br>
In other words, it's impossible to answer your question, I'm afraid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 5:36:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> For the case ..</span><hr size=1> .. where only good is available, it's more than OK -- you're doing the best you can.  For the case where both good and master are available, choosing to speak good is intensely annoying.  &quot;Good&quot; is only 61 skill.  It often has every letter garbled. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvordul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vordul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/27/02 12:32:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For the case ..</span><hr size=1> You sorta become adept at puzzling through the basics of what someone is saying.<br>
It gets much harder for idle conversation and specific instructions though.<br>
I know Elvish and Human, so I've never bothered with anything else since pretty much all of Starspun speaks Human really well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/27/02 1:08:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For the case ..</span><hr size=1> As you can perhaps already guess, some people in the game will give you a lot of grief if they have trouble understanding what you try to say to them.  So even if you have no trouble understanding them, it's still probably in your best interest to get your language skill up as high as possible, just so you don't have to hear them complain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwizardquendor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wizard Quendor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 12:07:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1188.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For the case ..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  it's still probably in your best interest to get your language skill up as high as possible, just so you don't have to hear them complain. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
